RACE.FOOTNOTES: SAILOR CHOW was off a step slow at the start then remained settled off the clear top pair, made a move and advanced into contention late on the turn, swung three to four wide into the lane, took the lead approaching the eighth pole and finished clear. NASTY EXAGGERATOR was allowed to settle off the early pace, swung four wide into the lane, responded willingly when called upon and produced a strong finish. FASCINATED vied inside of ROCK CITY ROCKET for the early lead racing well clear of the rest, continued to battle around the turn, could not match strides at the head of the lane, weakened but came back on to capture show. ROCK CITY ROCKET vied outside of FASCINATED for the early lead and continued to match strides around the turn, shook free to slight edge in upper stretch then was no match when the winner took over approaching the eighth pole. CAPTAIN DON raced off the clear top two leaders, saved ground around the turn, shifted out three wide and failed to rally.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 2 5F Dirt CR: 64. Maiden Special Weight Purse 33000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HER NAME WAS LOLA tracked the pace near the inside in early stages, angled out and circled up four wide to engage rivals for the lead near the quarter pole, battled for the lead heading into the lane, dueled for command with TRUE EMOTION in the final sixteenth, dug in gamely under firm handling and nipped foe for the win. TRUE EMOTION was forwardly placed racing just off the early leader, moved up to challenge for command late on the turn, battled for the lead into the lane, gained a slight edge past the furlong marker, fought on with HER NAME WAS LOLA in deep stretch, fought back gamely and got nipped on the wire. BE MY HUCKLEBERRY led the way in opening stages and continued to lead the way entering the turn, took on the challenge from a trio of pursuers near the quarter pole, fought back along the inside to the eighth pole, flattened off the top duo and just lasted for show. LOVE AMPLIFIED raced in contention just off the top pair, crept up three wide to challenge for the lead at the quarter pole, continued in striking distance in upper stretch then flattened out and got edged for show.
